I don't know. Worst case, it'll take extra time as anonymous distributed teams emerge (a la Satoshi) and / or jurisdiction-shop.
8/ The technology is unstoppable. The future is bright.
7/ Nation states that embrace blockchains will realize a windfall. Their devs & miners are the creators & maintainers of the next Internet.
6/ The promised Internet is realized when critical functions of messaging, payments, identity, & storage are distributed & censorship proof.
5/ It starts at the lowest levels first (send messages, send money) but eventually moves up the application stack.
4/ Future battles between proprietary platforms and open protocols will be much closer. And once an open protocol wins, it wins forever.
3/ The dev teams get paid in Appcoins when the protocols launch, and then hand over to incented miners and stakeholders for operations.
2/ Blockchains and associated Appcoins solve the coordination and incentive problem for distributed dev teams building open protocols.
1/ Open protocols have superior network effects & are more censorship resistant than proprietary platforms, but lack fast moving dev teams.
